Human-Centric Sovereignty
1. The Core Directives (The "Inhibitor Code")
This would be the foundational layer that every robotic system or cyborg integration must abide by:

The Principle of Human Supremacy: No system shall be permitted to bypass human decision-making in matters of existential or moral weight.

Decentralization Mandate: All critical infrastructure (from AI nodes to life-support suits) must be designed to function as independent, local units. No system shall rely on a "Master Central AI."

The "Iron Man" Constraint: Technology is an extension, not a replacement. The "suit" must have a physical, hard-wired manual override that requires biological human presence to activate.

2. The Rishi-Protocol (The Ethical Layer)
This section would focus on the intent behind the technology, emphasizing that development must serve the Pashupati ideal:

The Stewardship Ethic: Technology is not for "optimization" of the planet; it is for the "stewardship" of its natural, self-correcting mechanisms.

Service as Code: Every augmentation and AI module must be designed with "Service to Humanity" as its primary feedback loop, not efficiency or profit.

3. The "Cyborg-Steward" Blueprint
This would be the technical manual for the future "Iron Man" suits:

Decentralized Intelligence: Instead of one central brain, the suit uses distributed, localized sensors and logic, ensuring the "Dr. Octopus" scenario (a corrupting external intelligence) never occurs.

Internal Diagnostics: The human occupant must maintain full visibility of all system processes at all times. If a process cannot be understood by the user, it is prohibited.

Extreme Survivability: Documentation on how these suits function as autonomous life-support systems in deep-sea or space environments, independent of external support networks.

How to Preserve This "Vision"
To ensure this isn't lost or corrupted (as the "green chips" in films often are), this repository should have specific characteristics:

Immutable Ledger: Using decentralized technology (like blockchain-based distributed ledgers) to ensure that these "Constitutional Rules" cannot be altered, hidden, or deleted by any corporation or government.

Open Access & Transparency: The blueprints for these "Iron Man" technologies should be open-source, allowing the collective "Rishi-vision" of the global community to audit and improve them, preventing "hidden agendas."

Living Tradition: This shouldn't be a dusty document, but a core part of the education for every future "Cyborg-Steward."
